# cogbot-membership-website-template

A membership-gated website template powered by CogBot chat and IBM App ID authentication. Each deployment is a single client — customize it by editing `site.config.js`.

This template is a thin Vite shell on top of the **`@cogability/membership-kit`** npm package. The kit exports `<App>`, all pages, all auth, and all chat/SSE logic. The template owns: branding (`site.config.js`), static assets (`public/`), theme (`src/index.css`), the entry point (`src/main.jsx`), and the build (`vite.config.js`, `tailwind.config.js`).

If you need to change kit/SDK code itself, the source lives in [`CogAbility/cogability-packages`](https://github.com/CogAbility/cogability-packages), not in this repo.

---

## Architecture

- **React 19 + Vite 8** — static SPA, no server-side code in this repo
- **Tailwind CSS v3** — styling via CSS custom properties (design tokens in `src/index.css`)
- **React Router v7** — client-side routing, owned by the kit (`/` public, `/members` gated, `/onboarding`, `/profile`, `/callback`, `/access-denied`)
- **`@cogability/membership-kit`** — pages, components, auth, hooks, services
- **`@cogability/sdk`** — `CamClient`, `CmgClient`, `AuthClient` (no React deps)
- **IBM App ID (oidc-client-ts)** — OIDC popup login (handled by the kit)
- **CMG (CogBot Membership Gateway)** — external service that validates membership
- **CAM (CogBot Access Manager)** — external service that handles chat sessions and SSE streaming

Authentication flow (handled inside the kit, no template code involved):
```
User clicks Sign In
  → App ID popup (OIDC)
  → idToken stored in sessionStorage
  → POST to CMG /auth/validate with { idToken, namespace }
  → CMG returns { isMember, roles, geofenced, hasProfile, autoProvisioned }
  → ProtectedRoute + RoleGate gate the /members page
  → New auto-provisioned members redirect to /onboarding
```

---

## Where to make changes

### Change site content, branding, or SEO
Edit `site.config.js` at the project root. This is the file that differs between clients. It contains every user-visible string: site name, bot name, page title, meta description, OG tags, hero text, features, testimonials, about, member page copy, footer text, login messages, access-denied messages, etc.

The `meta` section controls the page title, description, and social sharing tags:
```js
meta: {
  title: 'Bot Name | Org Name',
  description: 'Description for search engines and social sharing.',
  ogImage: '/og-image.png',  // optional
}
```
If `meta` is omitted, title defaults to `botName | siteName` and description defaults to `hero.subtitle`. The Vite plugin in `vite.config.js` injects these into `index.html` at build time.

### Change colors or fonts
Edit the CSS custom properties in `src/index.css` under `:root`. Colors use HSL values:
```css
:root {
  --primary: 197 78% 53%;     /* main brand color */
  --secondary: 2 76% 58%;     /* accent color */
  --accent: 45 95% 62%;       /* highlight color */
}
```
The hero gradient adapts automatically to the `--primary` color.

### Change logos or images
Replace files in `public/`. Update the paths in `site.config.js` under `images:`:
- `public/bot-icon.svg`     — chat avatar and header icon
- `public/org-logo.svg`     — "Presented by" logo in the hero
- `public/favicon.svg`      — browser tab icon

### Change auth credentials
Edit `.env`. Never hardcode credentials in source files. The 6 required vars are all `VITE_*` (build-time injection) — see `.env.example`.

### Replace a whole page with a custom one
Use the `overrides` prop in `src/main.jsx`:
```jsx
import { App } from '@cogability/membership-kit';
import config from '@/site.config';
import MyMembersPage from './pages/MyMembersPage';

<App config={config} overrides={{ MembersPage: MyMembersPage }} />
```
Overridable: `Header`, `Footer`, `LandingPage`, `MembersPage`, `CallbackPage`, `OnboardingPage`, `ProfilePage`.

### Add a new route to this template
Routes are owned by the kit's internal `<App>`. To add app-level routes outside the kit, do NOT use `<App>` — instead compose the kit's pieces yourself in `src/main.jsx`:
```jsx
import { AuthProvider, ProtectedRoute, RoleGate, MembersPage } from '@cogability/membership-kit';
import { BrowserRouter, Routes, Route } from 'react-router-dom';

<BrowserRouter>
  <AuthProvider config={config}>
    <Routes>
      <Route path="/" element={<MyLanding />} />
      <Route path="/members" element={
        <ProtectedRoute><RoleGate><MembersPage /></RoleGate></ProtectedRoute>
      } />
      <Route path="/my-page" element={<MyPage />} />
    </Routes>
  </AuthProvider>
</BrowserRouter>
```

### Change kit or SDK code
Don't edit `node_modules/@cogability/...`. Open [`CogAbility/cogability-packages`](https://github.com/CogAbility/cogability-packages), make the change there, publish a new version, and `npm update` here.

---

## File guide (everything in this repo)

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `site.config.js` | All branding, content, and SEO — start here for any text or content change |
| `.env` | Service credentials — copy from `.env.example` and fill in values |
| `.env.example` | Documents the six required `VITE_*` env vars |
| `index.html` | HTML shell with `%SITE_TITLE%` / `%SITE_DESCRIPTION%` / `%FAVICON%` / `%OG_IMAGE%` placeholders, replaced at build time by the Vite plugin |
| `public/` | Logo and icon images (replace placeholders with your own) |
| `src/main.jsx` | Entry point — imports `{ App }` from the kit and renders `<App config={config} />` |
| `src/index.css` | Design tokens (colors, fonts) — edit to change the theme |
| `vite.config.js` | Build config, dev proxy (`/cogbot-api` → CAM), site-meta plugin |
| `tailwind.config.js` | Scans `index.html`, `src/**`, and `node_modules/@cogability/membership-kit/src/**` |
| `eslint.config.js` | ESLint flat config (React 19) |
| `postcss.config.js` | Tailwind + autoprefixer wiring |

Anything not listed here lives in `node_modules` and should not be edited.

---

## Deployment

**Platform hosting (Lovable, Vercel, Netlify, etc.):**
- Set all `VITE_*` variables from `.env.example` in your platform's build settings
- Build command: `npm run build`
- Output directory: `dist`
- After deploying, send your production URL to CogAbility for CORS configuration

**Running locally:**
```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Fill in .env with your credentials
npm install
npm run dev
```

For full local stack (CMG + CAM + frontend together): `npm run dev:all` (requires sibling `cmg-cogbot-membership-gateway` and `cam-cogbot-access-manager` repos checked out).

---

## Common tasks (for AI assistants)

- "Change the hero headline" → edit `hero.tagline` in `site.config.js`
- "Change the page title" → edit `meta.title` in `site.config.js`
- "Change the meta description" → edit `meta.description` in `site.config.js`
- "Add a testimonial" → add an item to `testimonials.items` in `site.config.js`
- "Change the primary color" → edit `--primary` in `src/index.css`
- "Change the CogBot" → update `VITE_COGBOT_ID` in `.env`
- "Change the sign-in button label" → edit `header.signInLabel` in `site.config.js`
- "Change the bot icon" → replace `public/bot-icon.svg`, update `images.botIcon` in `site.config.js`
- "Change the org logo" → replace `public/org-logo.svg`, update `images.orgLogo` in `site.config.js`
- "Add a new page" → see "Add a new route to this template" above (compose kit pieces in `src/main.jsx`)
- "Replace the members page" → use the `overrides` prop in `src/main.jsx`
- "Fix a bug in the chat widget" → it lives in the kit; open an issue or PR at `CogAbility/cogability-packages`
